Neka je $f_n(x) = \cos^n x + \cos^n(x + \frac{2\pi}{3}) + \cos^n(x + \frac{4\pi}{3})$ za $x \in \mathbb{R}$ i $n \in \mathbb{N}$.
\par
Neka $f_n(x)$ ne zavisi od $x$. Onda je $f_n(0) = f_n(-\frac{\pi}{3})$, pa je $1+2 \cdot(-\frac{1}{2})^n = (-1)^n+2 \cdot (-\frac{1}{2})^n$. Ako $2 \nmid n$, dobijena jednakost postaje $2 = \frac{4}{2^n}$, pa mora biti $n=1$. Ako $2 \mid n$, tj. ako je $n=2k$ za neko $k \in \mathbb{N}$, kako je $f_n(0) = f_n(-\frac{\pi}{6})$, sledi $1+2 \cdot \frac{1}{4^k} = 1+2 \cdot (-\frac{1}{2})^{2k} = (\frac{\sqrt{3}}{2})^{2k} + (-\frac{\sqrt{3}}{2})^{2k} = 2 \cdot (\frac{3}{4})^k$. Kako za $k \geqslant 3$ va\v{z}i $1+2 \cdot \frac{1}{4^k} > 1 > 2 \cdot (\frac{3}{4})^3 \geqslant 2 \cdot (\frac{3}{4})^k$, mora biti $n \in \{2,4\}$.
\par
Dakle, mora biti $n \in \{1,2,4\}$, a za ove vrednosti $f_n(x)$ ne zavisi od $x$, po\v{s}to je
\begin{footnotesize}
\begin{align*}
f_1(x) &= \cos x + \cos \left(x + \frac{2\pi}{3}\right) + \cos \left(x + \frac{4\pi}{3}\right) = 2\cos \left(x + \frac{2\pi}{3}\right) \cos \left(-\frac{2\pi}{3}\right) + \cos \left(x + \frac{2\pi}{3}\right)=0,\\
f_2(x) &= \cos^2 x + \cos^2 \left(x + \frac{2\pi}{3}\right) + \cos^2 \left(x + \frac{4\pi}{3}\right) = \frac{1+\cos 2x}{2} + \frac{1+\cos(2x+\frac{4\pi}{3})}{2} + \frac{1+\cos(2x+\frac{8\pi}{3})}{2}\\
&= \frac{3}{2} + \frac{1}{2} \cdot \left(\cos 2x + \cos \left(2x+\frac{4\pi}{3}\right) + \cos \left(2x+\frac{8\pi}{3}\right)\right) = \frac{3}{2} + \frac{1}{2} \cdot f_1(2x) = \frac{3}{2},\\
\text{i} \quad f_4(x) &= \left(\frac{1+\cos 2x}{2}\right)^2 + \left(\frac{1+\cos(2x+\frac{4\pi}{3})}{2}\right)^2 + \left(\frac{1+\cos(2x+\frac{8\pi}{3})}{2}\right)^2 = \frac{3}{4} + \frac{1}{2} \cdot f_1(2x) + \frac{1}{4} \cdot f_2(2x) = \frac{9}{8}.
\end{align*}
\end{footnotesize}

Va\v{z}i $A-Y-B$ i $\sphericalangle CYB = \sphericalangle YCA + \sphericalangle CAY = 60^\circ$, pa je $\sphericalangle BCY = 180^\circ - \sphericalangle CYB - \sphericalangle YBC = 58^\circ$, $\sphericalangle YBX = \sphericalangle YBC - \sphericalangle XBC = 59^\circ$ i $\sphericalangle BXY = 180^\circ - \sphericalangle XYB - \sphericalangle YBX = 61^\circ$. Primenom sinusne teoreme na $\triangle AYC$ i $\triangle YBC$, redom, sledi $\frac{AY}{YC} = \frac{\sin 29^\circ}{\sin 31^\circ}$ i $\frac{YB}{CY} = \frac{\sin 58^\circ}{\sin 62^\circ}$, pa je $\frac{AY}{YB} = \frac{\sin 29^\circ \sin 62^\circ}{\sin 31^\circ \sin 58^\circ} = \frac{2 \cos 31^\circ}{2 \cos 29^\circ} = \frac{\sin 59^\circ}{\sin 61^\circ}$. Primenom sinusne teoreme na $\triangle YBX$ sledi $\frac{XY}{YB} = \frac{\sin 59^\circ}{\sin 61^\circ}$. Dakle, va\v{z}i $\frac{AY}{YB} = \frac{XY}{YB}$, odnosno $AY=YX$.
\par
\textit{Drugo re\v{s}enje.} Neka je $x = \sphericalangle XAB \in (0^\circ, 31^\circ)$. Primenom sinusne teoreme na $\triangle ABX, \triangle BCX$ i $\triangle CAX$, sledi $\frac{XA}{BX} = \frac{\sin 59^\circ}{\sin x}$, $\frac{XB}{XC} = \frac{\sin 58^\circ}{\sin(3^\circ-x)}$ i $\frac{XC}{AX} = \frac{\sin (31^\circ-x)}{\sin 29^\circ}$, pa je $\sin 59^\circ \sin 58^\circ \sin(31^\circ - x) = \sin x \sin 3^\circ \sin 29^\circ$, odnosno $L(x) = 2\sin 59^\circ \cos 29^\circ \sin(31^\circ - x) = \sin 3^\circ \sin x = D(x)$.

\begin{minipage}{0.5\textwidth}
Kako je $2 \sin 59^\circ \cos 29^\circ > 0$ i $\sin 3^\circ > 0$ i kako $\sin(31^\circ - x)$ opada, a $\sin x$ raste na $(0^\circ, 31^\circ)$, sledi da jedna\v{c}ina $L(x) = D(x)$ ima najvi\v{s}e jedno re\v{s}enje na $(0^\circ, 31^\circ)$, a kako je $L(30^\circ) = 2 \sin 59^\circ \cos 29^\circ \sin 1^\circ = \sin 59^\circ \cdot (\sin 30^\circ - \sin 28^\circ) = \frac{1}{2} \sin 59^\circ - \frac{1}{2} \cdot (\cos 31^\circ - \cos 87^\circ) = \frac{1}{2} \cdot \sin 59^\circ - \frac{1}{2} \cdot \sin 59^\circ + \frac{1}{2} \cdot \sin 3^\circ = \sin 3^\circ \sin 30^\circ = D(30^\circ)$, ta jedna\v{c}ina ima ta\v{c}no jedno re\v{s}enje na $(0^\circ, 31^\circ)$ i to $x=30^\circ$.
\end{minipage}%
\begin{minipage}{0.5\textwidth}
\centering
\includegraphics{drzavno2022B4_5.png}
\end{minipage}

Sledi $\sphericalangle XAY = 30^\circ, \sphericalangle YXA = \sphericalangle XYB - \sphericalangle XAY = 30^\circ$, tj. $\triangle XYA$ je jednakokraki, pa je $AY=YX$.

